Okay so Iâve been waiting and wanting to post something specifically like this since a very long time. This has been quite a journey tho. The FIRST pic that you see is from December 2019 and the rest of the three are from 2020. So technically the two parts are just 1 year apart. ð¥
So... where do I even start man????? in the first part you just see a Hashir who is not too confident about himself, did not really like the way he looked, but yâknow you can always change the things that you do not intend to like or feel confident and nice about, that is exactly what I did. One day I woke up and said yeah! this is the day where I am gonna change the way I look because as I said I wasnât really confident or liked the way I looked because we all do realise shit, that inner voice telling us to carve ourselves out of whatever mess we are in. For me it was about maintenance and losing weight. Renascence. (woh alag baat hai dil toota tha ð¤«) 
This definitely requires extreme focus, dedication and devotion. Not easy. You have to say goodbye to all the burgers naalay paratay tay pizzay! all the âtreat py toh chalo na yaarâ. Iâd check my weight erryday just to stay motivated. IT IS WHAT IT IS. Saturday Nights in the GYM, not in some party. Because the end results will be worth it. Leave the temporary pleasure! ðð»
I was embarrassed to wear jeans or even slightly fitted clothes. I lost around 20 kgs. I will definitely not say that this the final form of mine or Iâm perfect, I endeavour to keep on getting better by erry passing day but but but, it is definitely a lil something I am proud of. ðð½â¤ï¸
Yâall, just please try to love yourself and the way you look, prioritise yourself, the day you prioritise yourself, youâll win. If you donât like the way you look, get up and CHANGE THAT. Stay patient during the process. You will get it ðâ¤ï¸
